14 This bill imposes strict liability on a person having
15 control over a hazardous substance for the reasonable response,
16 oversight, and monitoring costs expended by the state or
17 political subdivision related to hazardous conditions created
18 by that person. Under current law, a person having control
19 over a hazardous substance is strictly liable for excessive
20 and extraordinary costs expended by the state or political
21 subdivision resulting from responding at and to the scene of a
22 hazardous condition created by that person.
